[ProMED-mail thanks Drs Servies and Dierks for a more detailed description of the leptospirosis outbreak that occurred among US Marines at the Jungle Warfare Training Center in Okinawa, Japan.

The Jungle Warfare Training Center provides expert instruction to prepare Marine and Joint Forces for the rigors of combat in a dense jungle environment. It is located in Camp Gonsalves, in Northern Okinawa, Japan (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camp_Gonsalves). Camp Fuji is another installation of the United States Marine Corps adjacent to the Japan Ground Self-Defense Force Camp Takigahara, located in the Shizuoka Prefecture of Japan, at the base of Mount Fuji, on Honshu, the largest and most populous island of Japan (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camp_Fuji).

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2982249,25112. - Mod.ML]
